05/04/2006
STRASBOURG, France -- Council of Europe (CoE) Secretary General Terry Davis will pay a two-day official visit to Serbia-Montenegro starting on Thursday (6 April), according to a CoE press release. Davis will visit both Belgrade and Podgorica for meetings with officials representing the federal union and the two republics, and will deliver a speech to the federal parliament. 
Meanwhile, Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski is in Belgrade Wednesday for talks on bilateral economic co-operation and Euro-Atlantic integration issues. (CoE Web site, Beta - 04/04/06)
